5 Core Axes Calculations:
Token Economics[Cost Modelling]
Question it Answers:
How much text processing am I paying for?
Measures: Input Tokens - Output tokens - Token Cost - Monthly Spend
Total Cost = (Tokens per call) *(Calls per task)* (Tasks per day) * (Model Price)
→ A Linear Token calculation to validate that My Agentic System is chaotic/Expensive or Not.
Task decomposition Complexity [Workflow Complexity Designing]
Question it answers:
How much work is my System doing?
Measures: Number of Agents - Subtasks - orchestration depth - branching workflows
Total Work = Subtasks * Calls per subtask
→ As more subtasks usually increases: Cost - Latency - Failure Probability - Debugging Complexity. To reduce Calls per run.
Reliability Amplification [Retry/Failure Validation Designing]
Questions it Answers:
What happens when things fail?
Measures: Retry count - Tool Failures - Timeout Frequency - Fallback behavior.
Effective Cost = Base * Retry Factor
→ Avoid More Failures, as they eat your budget.
Latency Budgeting [ Distribution Time Designing]
Question it answers:
How long will the system take to respond?
Measures: Model Inference Time - Tool Execution Time - Network Delay - Sequential Chains.
Total Latency = Mean[ Stage Latency ] If Parallelized: =Max(Parallel branches)
→To avoid My Agent System Fail of Waiting.
5.Context Pressure Analysis [ Memory / Context Model ]
Question It Answers:
How much Information can My System Carry?
Measures: Context Window Usage - Retrieval Size - Prompt growth - Memory Accumulation
Context Usage = Prompt + Retrieved Data + History + Tool Output.
→ To Determine Chunking strategy, Retrieval Design, Summarizartion, Memory Architecture for Agentic C
